Date:4/12/2007 8:57:11 AM
From:gcrispin
RAS is a complicated company. They deal with both commercial and residential
mortgages. They acquired a portfolio of residential mortgages when the merged
with Taberna and the plan was to securitize these mortgages over the next three
or four years.

The reason I bought the stock was because less than one percent of their
residential mortgages were sub-prime. The recent AHM announcement has brought
the price of RAS down because it indicates that the metrics behind the
securitization, the selling of CDOs, are in question. What also comes into
question is the quality of mortgages they are holding. The aggregate score for
portfolio is 730 with 80/20 debt to equity ratio. You really don't know what
percentage is Alt-A loans.

Is this stock another AHM waiting to happen? I don't think so because only half
of their business is on the residential side, and RAS recently raised their
dividend in March, not cut their dividend like AHM. But questions persist in
what the CDO market will look like going forward. The AHM announcement was not
good for the market.

http://yahoo.reuters.com/news/articlehybrid.aspx?storyID=urn:newsml:reuters.com
20070412:MTFH41576_2.. .

I'm not impressed with the recent RAS announcement. One has to decide if this
is
an attempt to buy back stock or raise money. The buyback is small, so I'm not
impressed.

I currently have a small loss in my position and will see if the stock bounces
today. It's a good company in a bad sector. The problem is you don't know how
much worse the sector will get.
