--------
AG Edwards analyst Greg Mason said the key to determining whether the stock has
fallen too far is predicting what the company will do with its dividend. After
paying a quarterly dividend of $1.12 last quarter, American Home Mortgage said
it will pay a dividend of 70 cents this quarter.

Considering the stock closed at $19.55 Tuesday, Mason said an annual dividend
of $2.80 is fat. A stock that yields a dividend of 14.3 percent is attractive,
he said.

"The question remains, can the dividend fall further?" he wrote in a client
note. "We believe the answer is no." He expects payment defaults to decline as
the company stops lending to riskier borrowers. He forecasts some profit
deterioration, but believes the $2.80 annual dividend will remain intact.

He upgraded the stock to "Buy" from "Hold." His price target on the stock is
$23.50.

