I've added to my position in IMOS for the reasons I mentioned in my previous
post. The Carlyle group called off their purchase of ASE and the sector has
responded positively. Below is a link describing the book values of the sector.

http://www.forbes.com/markets/2007/04/18/ASE-carlyle-end-markets-equity-cx_jc_0
18markets1.html

IMOS trades at a striking discount to the group. Currently the stocks trades at
1.2 book value, yet is expected to grow 20% this year.

http://finance.yahoo.com/q/ks?s=IMOS

The company has a complicated corporate structure that they have simplified
with a purchase of a shared subsidiary. This purchase should add to earnings
this year. The Yahoo board has a very knowledgable group posting on the
company.
